<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-13T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-13T16:00:00-05:00" n="947" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d947">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/8175</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Arredondo</persName>, representing American
                                interests</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-13T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>548. Department informed that authorities in Sonora in June, last, seized
                            all arms and ammunition belonging to American settlers at Esperanza and
                            vicinity. Settlers urgently need arms for protection against Yaqui
                            Indians.</p>
                        <p>Request appropriate authorities to order immediate return to settlers
                            mentioned of all arms and ammunition taken from them in June.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>